  "html": "<!-- TODO (EJ): split from \"Terminal Tools\" — add your voice + a still image.\n     README only has a .mov demo, which the filmstrip can't show yet. Draft. -->\n<p class=\"\">For presentations and livestreaming: show every key you press as large ASCII art on screen, so an audience can follow along.</p>\n<figure role=\"figure\" aria-label=\"How it works — pynput captures keys, pyfiglet renders them as centered ASCII art\" class=\"\">\n<img src=\"https://res.cloudinary.com/ejf/image/upload/c_scale,f_auto,q_auto:good,w_1280/projects/showtouch/code.png\" alt=\"How it works — pynput captures keys, pyfiglet renders them as centered ASCII art\" loading=\"lazy\" decoding=\"async\" srcset=\"https://res.cloudinary.com/ejf/image/upload/c_scale,f_auto,q_auto:good,w_640/projects/showtouch/code.png 640w, https://res.cloudinary.com/ejf/image/upload/c_scale,f_auto,q_auto:good,w_960/projects/showtouch/code.png 960w, https://res.cloudinary.com/ejf/image/upload/c_scale,f_auto,q_auto:good,w_1280/projects/showtouch/code.png 1280w, https://res.cloudinary.com/ejf/image/upload/c_scale,f_auto,q_auto:good,w_1920/projects/showtouch/code.png 1920w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 430px) 92vw, (max-width: 768px) 85vw, 900px\" title=\"How it works — pynput captures keys, pyfiglet renders them as centered ASCII art\" width=\"1400\" height=\"900\" style=\"--splay-rot:-2.45deg;\" data-dimensions=\"1400×900\" class=\"img-full my-8 rounded-sm img-splay w-full mx-auto py-4\" crossorigin=\"anonymous\">\n<figcaption class=\"\">How it works — pynput captures keys, pyfiglet renders them as centered ASCII art</figcaption>\n</figure>",
